# X-Ways X-Tension Builder Skill — project notes

> Copy this file to `CLAUDE.md` (git-ignored) to give Claude Code project-level
> instructions when working in this repo.

This repo is the **`xways-xtension-authoring` skill** + starter templates + a
distilled X-Tension knowledge base. It does **not** contain working X-Tensions,
the X-Ways SDK, or the X-Ways manuals.

## Rules

- **Don't commit copyrighted X-Ways material.** The SDK header (`X-Tension.h`),
  manuals, and user-forum content are copyright X-Ways AG. The `docs/` notes are
  distilled / empirical only and cite official sources by link. See
  [docs/getting-the-sdk.md](docs/getting-the-sdk.md).
- **Don't commit binaries, secrets, local paths, or case data.** Run
  `.claude/skills/xways-xtension-authoring/scripts/prepublish-scan.ps1 -Strict`
  before any push.
- **Templates are the read-only scaffold source** under
  [templates/x-tensions/](templates/x-tensions/). Scaffold new X-Tensions into
  your OWN project, not this repo.
- **API correctness:** never invent `XWF_*` calls or flags. Verify against
  `docs/`, the live API page, or your locally-acquired SDK header — see the
  [API guardrail](.claude/skills/xways-xtension-authoring/references/api-guardrail.md).

## Conventions

The reusable patterns live in [docs/conventions/](docs/conventions/index.md) and
are the single source of truth. The skill cites them by symbol; the convention
pages cite the `wrapper` template, so nothing drifts.
